-- Thailand Stocks: Kasikornbank, Pico, PTT, PTT Exploration
-- B y   T o n y   J o r d a n
-- 2012-06-11T10:19:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-11/khon-kaen-sugar-pico-ptt-exploration-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand   trading.  Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close.  The  SET Index (SET)  rose 2.8 percent to 1,158.07, the biggest
gain in seven months.  Kasikornbank Pcl (KBANK)  , Thailand’s fourth-largest bank
by total assets, rose 4.3 percent to 157 baht, the biggest gain
since April 30. The lender led a group including Industrial &
Commercial Bank of China (Thai) and Land & Houses Bank that will
provide 2.46 billion baht ($78 million) of loans to Electricity
Generating Pcl to fund solar power projects.  Pico (Thailand) Pcl (PICO)  , an event-management company,
rose 2.5 percent to 3.24 baht, its biggest gain in almost three
weeks. The company will pay a cash dividend of 0.1 baht per
share for the six months ended April 30, it said in a statement
today.  PTT Exploration & Production Pcl (PTTEP)  , the nation’s
biggest publicly listed explorer, rose 4.7 percent to 168 baht,
its largest increase in six months. Cove Energy Plc, the U.K.
explorer that agreed to be bought by PTT Exploration, said it
found more gas at the Rovuma Area 1 exploration block off the
coast of  Mozambique . Shares of parent company  PTT Pcl (PTT)  
jumped 3.6 percent to 320 baht.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony Jordan in Bangkok at 
